There is a certain very modern (mostly American) sentiment of "removing words from your dictionary", for example thanking people for their patience instead of saying you're sorry for being late, not saying "I'll try" to seem bolder or not using "to be honest" to seem as always so

Its big 2 problems are:

1. It seeks to *ERADICATE* sadness, uncertainty, etc. instead of just *minimize* and confine them to their healthy role

2. It succeeds only in disbalancing the linguistic harmony, expressing the same old statements with different more pompous exterior
Google "5 phrases to remove from your vocabulary", people legit fall for it
